==English==
===Noun===
'''angle''' (''plural'' '''angles''')

#{{geometry}} A [[figure]] formed by two [[ray]]s that start from a common [[point]] (a '''plane angle''') or by three [[plane]]s that [[intersect]] (a '''solid angle''').
#:''the angle between lines A and B''
#{{geometry}} The [[measure]] of such a figure.
#:''The angle between lines A and B is 45 degrees.''
#A [[corner]] where two walls intersect.
#:''an angle of a building''
#A change in [[direction]].
#:''The horse took off at an angle.''
#A [[viewpoint]].
#:''Look at it from this angle.''

